Analysis of unemployment and inflation rate data¶

Visualizing Iowa unemployment and inflation rate in a line plot:¶

In [43]:
dfiu_IA.plot(kind='line',title='IA Unemployment vs. National Inflation Rate')
plt.show()
  • unemployment in Iowa does seem to move in tandem with the national inflation rate
  • inflation has sharper changes in direction than Iowa unemployment

Visualizing United States unemployment and inflation rate in a line plot:¶

In [44]:
dfiu_us.plot(kind='line', title='US Unemployment vs. National Inflation Rate')
plt.show()
  • the difference between unemployment and inflation rate is more prominent when assessing national unemployment
  • we note that these plots also show that Iowa unemployment tends to be significantly lower than national unemployment
  • changes in inflation tend to have a similar impact on national unemployment, but the effects are somewhat lagged

Assessing correlation between Iowa unemployment and inflation by creating a scatter plot:¶

In [45]:
dfiu_IA.plot(kind='scatter', x='Inflation Rate', y='IA Unemployment', title = "Correlation Between National Inflation Rate and Iowa Unemployment Rate", grid=True, figsize=(10,10))

ANALYSIS

The national unemployment rate had an overall downward trend until the '08 recession. Eventually the unemployment rate came back down the where it had been pre-housing crash, with Covid looming in the future.
